    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our premier offensive anchor. His score of 80.93 is the clear standout, buoyed by an ideal matchup against Petty, whose 6.57 xERA provides the most favorable environment of the day. With a +19% boost from the opposing pitcher\u2019s skill and a dynamic platoon advantage, he is an essential start, especially given our focus on elite sprint speed to capture the scarce SB category. Complementing him is **Trea Turner** (66.43), whose position in the leadoff spot against Junk offers high-ceiling potential for runs, while **Carson Benge** (67.24) capitalizes on a high-park-factor environment and favorable pitcher dynamics to round out our top-tier trio.\n\nWhile **Yordan Alvarez** (60.60) faces a tougher test against Yamamoto, his elite xwOBA of 0.427 ensures he remains a locked-in start despite the SP\u2019s quality. We are monitoring the lower end of our lineup closely, particularly **Colt Keith** (42.25) and **Hyeseong Kim** (41.47), both of whom are operating near the marginal threshold. **Caleb Durbin** was the most difficult bench omission; while he profiles well, his exclusion from the active starting lineup meant he could not overcome the -100% adjustment, forcing us to favor the confirmed presence of **Chase Meidroth** (42.26) for roster efficiency. \n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the platoon disadvantages impacting **Colt Keith** and **Hyeseong Kim** against left-handed starters today. Additionally, while **Dillon Dingler** (56.77) holds a solid score, he faces Tolle, an arm that requires careful observation throughout the game. With **Christian Yelich** sidelined on the IL and **Zac Veen** remaining in the minors, our depth is tested; we will rely on **Junior Caminero** (63.97) and **Kyle Schwarber** (63.08) to provide the necessary power surge to mitigate the risk of a low-scoring performance from the bottom of the order.",
